author: Freddie Clayton
description: Democrats investigating Jeffrey Epstein have intensified their calls for Britain's former prince, Andrew Mountbatten Windsor, to answer their questions about his links to the disgraced financier, days after King Charles stripped his younger brother of his title
title: Andrew faces pressure as new emails to Epstein are published and Democrats call on him to testify

author: Freddie Clayton
description: Canadian Prime Minister Mark Carney has said he apologized to President Donald Trump for an Ontario government ad that used former President Ronald Reagan's words in order to criticize Trump’s trade policy."I did apologize," Carney told reporters on Saturday after attending the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation Summit in Gyeongju, South Korea
title: Canada's Mark Carney apologizes to Trump over anti-tariff ad
